        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:16PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Monumental Peak, or 25 miles north of Lowman, moving west at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Horsethief Reservoir around 430 PM MDT.
Cascade around 440 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
